<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7270907>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Stolella himalayana, holotype, now Rumarcanella himalayana, Specimen No. P1388. (a) Floatoblast valves, scale bar = 100 µm; (b) SEM image of a floatoblast dorsal valve; (c) close-up of a portion of the floatoblast fenestra showing hypertubercles, the key feature of the genus Rumarcanella, scale bar = 10 µm; (d) Floatoblast suture showing the very lumpy structure; (e) Detail of the floatoblast profile showing the serrated appearance, scale bar = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7270907/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7270909>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Stolonate growth in Plumatella vaihiriae from Silver Lake, Cowlitz County, Washington, USA. The species is known for its normally robust, often bushy colonies. Photo has been digitally enhanced to increase contrast. Scale bar = 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7270909/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

